 Import Inventory Database using this command in terminal.
	mongorestore --db inv  ~/mongodb/day2/inv
	
 select products with price greater than 1000 and less than 5000.
	db.products.find({price : {$gt : 1000, $lt : 50000}}).pretty()
	
 display products which have phone number for vendor “using 2 ways ”
	db.products.find({"vendor.phone" : {$exists : true}}).pretty()
	db.products.find({"vendor.phone" : {$ne: null}}).pretty()
	
 display products which available in 4 stocks at the same time.
	db.products.find({stock : {$size : 4}}).pretty()

 increase all products by 500 EGP.
	db.products.updateMany({},{ $inc: { price: 500 } })

 replace stock #30 with #60 in all products.
	db.products.update({"stock": 30},{ $set: { 'stock.$': 60 }})
	
 remove stock 70 from all products.
	db.products.updateMany({}, { $pull: { stock: 70 } })
	
 display only product name and vendor phone number.
	db.products.find({"vendor.phone": {$exists: true}}, { name: 1, "vendor.phone": 1}).pretty()
	    
 display the most expensive product.
	db.products.find({}).sort({price: -1}).limit(1).pretty()
	
 Import books from json file into new database use mongoimport.
	mongoimport --db lib -c books /home/mohab/mongodb/day2/books.json --jsonArray
	
 Create text index on shortDescription field
	db.books.createIndex({"shortDescription": "text"})
	
 Retrieve all books which have“android”
	db.books.find({$text: {$search: "android"}}).pretty()
	
 Retrieve all books which have "web applications" exactly
	db.books.find({$text: {$search: "\"web applications\""}}).pretty()

